              and Deng, Grace and Feng, Mei-Ling E. and Gupta, Rajesh K.
              and Hong, Dezhi and McGranaghan, Ryan M. and Owolabi, Olukunle O.
              and Qu, Tianyi and Ren, Wei and Schafer, Toryn L. J.
              and Sharma, Ashutosh and Shen, Chaopeng and Sherman, Mila Getmansky
              and Sunter, Deborah A. and Wang, Lan and Matteson, David S.},
  title    = {Critical {R}isk {I}ndicators ({CRI}s) for the electric power grid:
              a survey and discussion of interconnected effects},
  journal  = {Environment Systems and Decisions},
  year     = {2021},
  doi      = {10.1007/s10669-021-09822-2},
  url      = {https://doi.org/10.1007/s10669-021-09822-2},
  abstract = {The electric power grid is a critical societal resource connecting
              multiple infrastructural domains. This paper provides a survey of
              models and methods that seek to explore the significant interconnected
              impact of the electric power grid and interdependent domains, providing
              relevant critical risk indicators (CRIs) across diverse domains
              including climate, ecology, hydrology, finance, space weather, and
              agriculture.}}

